==Spanish-language books==
In 1984, Parker Brothers' ''Tales from the Care Bears'' made their appearance in Spain as the ''Un Cuento de Los Osos Amorosos'' series.  The titles in this version were published by that country's division of General Mills, and translated from the original English by Leopoldo Rodríguez Regueira.<ref name=amiga>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldcat.org/title/amiga-para-laura/oclc/19096479|title=Catalog information for ''Una Amiga para Laura''|accessdate=August 10, 2010|work=WorldCat|publisher=Online Computer Library Center (OCLC)}}</ref><ref name=bruja>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldcat.org/title/bruja-en-la-calle/oclc/15117329|title=Catalog information for ''Una Bruja en la Calle''|accessdate=August 10, 2010|work=WorldCat|publisher=Online Computer Library Center (OCLC)}}</ref><ref name=hermanita>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldcat.org/title/hermanita-para-oscar/oclc/15117278|title=Catalog information for ''Una Hermanita para Oscar''|accessdate=August 10, 2010|work=WorldCat|publisher=Online Computer Library Center (OCLC)}}</ref>

